reviewText: This play was well written, and it touched on a subject that is among us today. A young married couple living the high life, until the husband loses his high powered job and the money that was saved is almost gone because wife is spending like she Is a Rockerfeller, and living under her parents. The marriage goes through a strain, and Latoya Luckett character threatens to leave because she can't have red bottom shoes and go on girl weekend vacations.  This is more of a dramedy than comedy. see it, you will not be disappointed.
Title: For Richer or Poorer

Title: For Richer or Poorer

reviewText: Aubrey (Rockmund Dunbar) and Kya (LeToya Luckett) have been married less than five years. Everything is going well financially until Aubrey loses his high paying job. Now, adjustments must be made and Kya is not pleased. A marriage tested. Will they be able to work things out or will they go their separate ways?GMC TV (now called UP, meaning Uplifting Entertainment) airs stage plays - For Richer or Poorer is one of the best I've seen. Talented cast (Dunbar, in particular, and it was nice to see gospel music artist, Karen Clark Sheard, who made her television acting debut), thought-provoking and funny at times. It became a series and I watched, but I enjoyed this play much more.
Title: For Richer or Poorer
